<h2>Topical Authority vs Domain Authority</h2>
<p>These two concepts get confused constantly. They measure different things.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Topical authority vs domain authority comparison showing key differences" src="/images/blog/topical-authority-vs-domain-authority.webp" /></p>
<p><strong>Domain Authority (DA)</strong> is a third-party metric created by Moz. It scores the overall strength of a website from 1 to 100 based on backlink profile, domain age, and site-wide signals. Ahrefs calls their version Domain Rating (DR). Semrush calls theirs Authority Score.</p>
<p><strong>Topical authority</strong> is not a single score. It is Google's internal assessment of how well your site covers a specific subject. There is no public metric for it. You cannot see your topical authority score in any tool.</p>
